social_posts.post_text: @damiandtla was absolutely excellent - I highly recommend! Banana leaf flan with sesame caramel ended a perfect meal filled with fish tartare tostadas, duck al pastor, pescado a la brasa made with dry aged branzino, kimchi martinis (!!!) and more. Thanks for celebrating with me @christian_gillespie 🖤😘
Add @lacheatday to your list of must-try LA burgs if you haven't already. A+ stuff.
Happy holidays from @proofbakeryla's life-changing canelés.

Chewy toasted sesame cookies from @jesseszewczyk's Cookies book. These are an absolute delight and I have a feeling they're going to be requested over and over again at all holiday gatherings. If you are a black sesame dessert fan, you absolutely need to make them. 🖤
This year's cookie selection: neapolitan sugar cookies, chewy toasted sesame cookies, ginger molasses cookies, & buttery strawberry cornmeal thumbprints. Happy holidays!! ♥️💕❤️‍🔥🥂
Lucky 13. Happy anniversary bb. 💕

Two of my weekend favorites from @cecis_gastronomia: suppli, aka fried tomato risotto stuffed with mozzarella, and torta della nonna, a custard cake with lemon and pine nuts. Both incredibly delicious and impossible to pass up.
Best friends (sometimes).

Attended a truly bomb preview of the new @isla.losangeles pop-up in the cozy home of @annienorthropblack & @courtneynorthropblack. Everything was cooked over a wood fire, served family style, and as delicious as it was stunning. Check their bio for reservations for the next pop-up if you love things like smoked duck served ssam-style, grilled spot prawns, skewered trumpet mushrooms, milk-brined and roasted cauliflower, smoked mussels, whole kanpachi stuffed with greens, and so much more.
Paul and Luda are decidedly not fans of the snow 🌨️❄️

We may have overdone it on the skewers at the appropriately named @little_skewer but we'll be back to finish the job. Skewered cumin lamb, tofu skin, chicken wings, corn (!), pork belly, and more with plentiful sides like smashed cucumber, egg crepe, cold noodles, cheese corn, and scallops with vermicelli noodles. And beer, lots of beer.

@linguafrancarestaurant made for one of our best date nights in a while, I can't recommend it enough. I was a big fan of the juicy burger on a sesame seed English muffin with extra skinny, extra crispy fries, but we also loved the lavash with cured albacore and turmeric ginger cream cheese (!!) and the sweet potato rarebit with a fried duck egg. We also had an affagato for dessert with @mashtimalones date ice cream, but that got inhaled immediately. 10/10.

A rare Westside weeknight luxury at @sushitama_la. We did the table omakase (with an uni addition) and every bite was truly phenomenal. That piece of toro was so rich and fatty, it almost tasted like a cheeseburger. If you're looking to impress your next dinner date, this is the place to go.
Lunch with a side of grocery shopping at @thefishking. Crunchy fried scallops, fries, and a soy ginger poke bowl. 🤌
Tahini Banana Bread. Nutty and still very banana-y with sesame seeds throughout for a lovely texture. Yet another @acozykitchen recipe that I adore. 🍌🍌
Spice is the best hangover cure 🌶️🌶️
Preparing for summer.

If you love seafood (especially shrimp, like me) I recommend you stop by @loreto_frogtown the next time you're looking for something delicious (and spicy). We got shrimp tostadas, shrimp tacos and aguachile (more shrimp, of course), with a side of elote and potato soup because it sounded so good - all fantastic! I applaud the many ways in which I am able to enjoy shrimp here 👏

Happy birthday @notkramer!! I love you more and more every year. Thank you for always putting me and the dogs first, for letting me make all food-based decisions in our relationship, and for always being willing to run out to get an ingredient I forgot to buy when I'm cooking or baking. ♥️♥️ You're the best.

Happy to report that @yess.restaurant is not skimping on the mala sauce! We scooped every last spoonful of this spicy, crunchy topping up with @meijitofu (I even saved the dish so I could spoon it over other bites). The miso cod was 10/10 as well (rich, buttery, all the good things), the fish "katsu" was extra crispy and crunchy, and beef flank was perfectly medium rare. This meal was definitely an experience and perfect for Kramer's big 3-6 birthday dinner ♥️
A quick trip means you only have time for the essentials.

Brown butter banana bread with streusel topping from @sarah_kieffer's new book, #100morningtreats, which I'm already obsessed with and plan on making 99 more recipes from. But I'm always excited about a new banana bread recipe, so I had to start with this one. It's absolutely delightful, of course.

@de_buena_planta has still got it - it's a great spot to chill with a cocktail on a beautiful summertime patio, people watch, and snack on (mostly) vegan tacos and quesadillas (there's cheese for us non-plant based people, don't worry).

The long weekend diet.

Banana pudding, hot dogs, sour cream and onion potato salad.

I highly recommend adding a layer of fresh cherries to your favorite pound cake recipe. I prefer any recipe that includes sour cream (I used Martha's) because the tanginess is A+ alongside sweet, juicy summer-ish cherries (it's still dreary in LA so we're still waiting for summer).
Hire us for your next wedding, bar mitzvah, retirement party or miscellaneous event.
Mixed berry bars with a brown sugar crust were my dessert highlight this week. Like a pie, but handheld and bite-size (ish). Recipe by @mstanyaholland. 🍓🫐🍒
Summer things. Musubi from @alohacateringservices, brunch from @stanleyswetgoods, helmet nachos, hot dogs, dinner at @foundoyster, actual dogs, and yes - Smirnoff ice jello shots. ☀️🕶️
Hello, gorgeous 👀♥️ @bubandgrandmasbread
Definitely add peanut butter m&ms to your favorite chocolate chip cookie recipe (mine is in my highlights, as always).
We may have over ordered but the pre and post-beach snacks were extremely on point.

Blueberry, blackberry and raspberry muffins topped with crunchy lemon-ginger sugar. This recipe from @justine_snacks is an excellent rainy day baking activity, after which you're rewarded with bite after bite of sweet, juicy summer deliciousness. Search "blueberry muffins" on her site for the recipe (I'll also link in my stories).
Absolutely blown away by all the delicious things to eat (and drink) at @barrasantosla. 🦐☀️🍷
WFI (working from @isla.losangeles). The skewer and seafood selection is as strong as their wifi connection.
Head to toe SPF ❤️‍🔥
My favorite Sunday tradition is getting @proofbakeryla sandwiches with @tarenater and @notkramer. There's nothing better.
It's finally chocolate chip cookie season. Recipe in my highlights as always.
An absolutely bangin bánh mì from @vuive.eats! Everything from this spot rules but this cold cut combo might be my all time favorite.
Only the classics last night at @donnas_ep 🍝

Some cool people sent me a bird from @pastureproject and I have to say, these chickens are 10/10. Juicy, flavorful and ready for the oven. This is the kind of dinner that you make and eat so much of while you're still in the kitchen that you're full before you sit down at the table, which is fine by me because that means more couch time. I recommend serving with charred carrots and onions or whatever winter veg you have in the fridge. Also if you order one use the code JUICYCHICKEN for 20% off!
It really was a Sexy Unique Reunion.
Best trip with the best people ❤️
The biggest and best tuna sandwich on thinly sliced challah with a side of doughnuts and croissants ❤️🤌

We got it all and loved every bite from @lawrencebarbecue. Sticky ribs, brisket, pulled pork, wings, raw and grilled oysters (with BBQ butter), and all the sides and sauces. Truly a delight during a quick trip to Durham, NC!

A beachy holiday happy hour at @bellesbeachhouse with the gals ♥️ Our very California spread included mochiko chicken nuggets, spicy tuna crispy rice, watermelon "tuna" sashimi (possibly my favorite), crispy rock shrimp with spicy aioli and, of course, a couple of tiki drinks and lots of good people watching.
These zebra-striped shortbread cookies from @moroccochris are 10/10. Plus they pull double duty as both delicious cookies and festive table decoration 🎅🦓
A perfect last lunch of 2023 from @littlefish_echopark.
Happy New Year to my friends and Bad New Year to my enemies 👍 (thx for the pix @romanmf)
Happy 14th wedding anniversary @notkramer 🤴👸 Here's to 15, 16, 17, 18, 19, 20 and all the rest. Ilu!
